      • matchesPath

        public boolean matchesPath(EnumSet<Pathspec.FlagT> flags,
                           @Nonnull
                           String path)
        Try to match a path against a pathspec

        Unlike most of the other pathspec matching functions, this will not fall back on the native case-sensitivity for your platform. You must explicitly pass flags to control case sensitivity or else this will fall back on being case sensitive.

        Parameters:
        flags - Combination of git_pathspec_flag_t options to control match
        path - The pathname to attempt to match
        Returns:
        true if path matches spec, false if it does not

      • matchWorkdir

        public List<String> matchWorkdir(@Nonnull
                                 Repository repo,
                                 EnumSet<Pathspec.FlagT> flags)
        Match a pathspec against the working directory of a repository.

        This matches the pathspec against the current files in the working directory of the repository. It is an error to invoke this on a bare repo. This handles git ignores (i.e. ignored files will not be considered to match the `pathspec` unless the file is tracked in the index).

        Parameters:
        repo - The repository in which to match; bare repo is an error
        flags - Combination of git_pathspec_flag_t options to control match
        Returns:
        a list of matches
        Throws:
        GitException - GIT_ENOTFOUND if no matches and the GIT_PATHSPEC_NO_MATCH_ERROR flag was given
